02/Oct/18 3:57 PM;MattChild;It appears to be messed up because of Line 459 on SearchInterface.cs:

var templatePath = Path.Combine(Config.SolrHome, CORE_TEMPLATE_PATH);

This is using the SolrHome in the web config to map a relative path to the solr folder. This works on our local servers because we have the solr home directory in the www root. However, for STIG purposes, the SOLR installation needs to be elsewhere (which is how it is configured on NSERC). You can't provide an absolute path here, however, because the web config is expecting it to be a relative one.

